    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "By 1912 the little village of Delta lay beneath a large lake, rightfully called Lake Delta.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://oneida.nygenweb.net/towns/lee/deltahistory.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Delta once housed the United States' second‑oldest cheese factory, built at the foot of Short Hill Road.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://oneida.nygenweb.net/towns/lee/deltahistory.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1891, Delta's corn canning factory processed 400,000 cans, employing roughly 100 people by the next year.",
